Subject: [duckbridge][fe] Whitelist catalog type "duckbridge" in SPI_READY_TYPES

What:
  Adds "duckbridge" to CatalogFactory.SPI_READY_TYPES so that
  CREATE CATALOG ... type="duckbridge" is routed to the fe-connector SPI
  (a PluginDrivenExternalCatalog around our ServiceLoader-discovered
  DuckBridgeConnectorProvider) instead of being rejected as an unknown type.

Why upstream needs it:
  SPI_READY_TYPES is a hard-coded allowlist; the SPI silently ignores any
  ConnectorProvider whose getType() is not in the set (no connector-declared
  registration seam exists yet). Without this entry the plugin never loads.
  "jdbc" is already whitelisted but routes to the in-tree fe-connector-jdbc, so
  we use a distinct type ("duckbridge") + this one-line patch rather than
  colliding with it. This is a READ-ONLY connector, so it needs ONLY this
  whitelist entry -- the pluginCatalogTypeToEngine() CREATE-TABLE patch that
  doris-ducklake carries is deliberately NOT included here (plan Deploy shape:
  a read-only connector needs only the whitelist guard).

Upstream ask / exit criteria:
  Generalize SPI_READY_TYPES to a connector-declared capability/registration
  seam so a new SPI full-adopter does not need an FE source edit. When that
  lands (and a Doris release ships the fe-connector SPI), this patch is deleted
  and BASELINE points at the release tag.

Anchor at pin 5f009592035:
  fe/fe-core/src/main/java/org/apache/doris/datasource/CatalogFactory.java
  private static final Set<String> SPI_READY_TYPES =
      ImmutableSet.of("jdbc", "es", "trino-connector", "max_compute", "paimon", "iceberg", "hms");
  (upstream set as of this pin: {jdbc, es, trino-connector, max_compute,
   paimon, iceberg, hms}; "hms" was added by the Hive P11 migration.)

Apply:  git apply --3way doris-patches/fe/0001-spi-ready-types-duckbridge.patch
